      0.9248120267656803,
      0.23691860485868513
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_bf784eedb0c377adb9a0f286954af785_1",
    "order": 8
  },
  {
    "chunk_id": "docling_newspaper_bf784eedb0c377adb9a0f286954af785_1_4",
    "text": "The purpose of the matching program is to provide each participating state agency administering TANF with new hire, quarterly wage, and unemployment insurance information from OCSE's NDNH system of records to assist them in establishing or verifying TANF applicants' and recipients' eligibility for assistance, reducing · New hire processed date payment errors, and maintaining · Employee name and address program integrity, including determining whether duplicate · Employee date and state of hire participation exists or if the applicant or · Federal and State employer recipient resides in another state. The identification numbers state TANY agencies may also use the · Department of Defense code NDH information for the secondary purpose of updating the recipients' · Employer name and address reported participation in work activities · Transmitter agency code and updating recipients' and their · Transmitter state code employers' contact information maintained by the state TANF agencies. · Transmitter state or agency name",
    "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
    "bbox": [
      0.07123174709830976,
      0.15401785721086578,
      0.603513930330577,
      0.4188523011090921
    ],
    "page": "newspaper_bf784eedb0c377adb9a0f286954af785_1",
    "order": 9
  },
